cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with synthesizing novel views of an object from a single monocular image using visual information and an Image Completion Network. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper involves rendering 2.5D sketches from a 3D CAD to guide the image synthesis process. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the Image Completion Network is a deep learning model. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper involves using a-priori visual information to guide the image synthesis process. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper mentions the ability to handle a wide range of 3D transformations, which could be relevant in robotics applications.
